reviewText: A good introduction to 1950's action television show about the adventures of RCMP Mountie and his wonderful lead dog in both winter and summer..

This DVD cost 50 cents, and that's about how much it was worth-quality wise.  The color is not restored.  It's faded and irregular.  You can still hear the sound track-thankfully.  It was a nice trip down memory lane to see this show I remember from my childhood, but I was disappointed in the quality.  I'm glad I didn't spend much.
